%N A398018 Decimal expansion of -Sum_{k>=1} lambda(k) * d(k)^2 * log(k) / k^2, where lambda is Liouville's function (A008836), and d(k) is the number of divisors of k (A000005).
%H A398018 Matthew Perkins and Robert A. Van Gorder, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s11139-018-0037-4">Closed-form calculation of infinite products of Glaisher-type related to Dirichlet series</a>, The Ramanujan Journal, Vol. 49, No. 2 (2019), pp. 371-389. See p. 380, Corollary 2.8.
%F A398018 Equals (4*Pi^4/1125) * (log(2*Pi) + gamma + 24*log(A) + 360*log(A_3), where gamma is Euler's constant (A001620), A is the Glaisher-Kinkelin constant (A074962), and A_3 is the third Bendersky constant (A243263).
%F A398018 Note that Sum_{k>=1} lambda(k) * d(k)^2 / k^2 = 2*Pi^4/1125.
%e A398018 0.328649680826302964312276331373616411958514406826698...
%t A398018 RealDigits[(4*Pi^4/1125) * (Log[2*Pi] + EulerGamma + 24*Log[Glaisher] - 360*Zeta'[-3] - 11/2), 10, 120][[1]]
%o A398018 (PARI) (4*Pi^4/1125) * (log(2*Pi) + Euler - 24*zeta'(-1) - 360*zeta'(-3) - 7/2)
%Y A398018 Cf. A000005, A001620, A008836, A035116, A073002 (Sum_{k>=1} log(k)/k^2), A074962, A243263, A398010, A398012, A398013.
